main event: A sighting report was filed for an object observed over Long Beach, California on November 6, 1957, which was concluded to be a conventional aircraft by observers.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 15 minutes, The object was believed to be a conventional aircraft as per the report, Both the officer of the day and the airdrome officer looked for the reported object but saw nothing, The report indicated only one lone star was visible that night, Capt. F. W. Brown, the duty controller, suggested the object might have been a balloon.
witness description: officers at the airdrome and control
